text: Sela Molisa (15 December 1950 â€“ 21 August 2022) was a Vanuatuan politician. He was a member of the Parliament of Vanuatu from 1982 to 2012."Vanuatu MP to monitor charter", Fiji Times, 12 June 2008"Molisa wins Vanuatu seat", Fiji Times, 13 September 2008 He was the minister of finance from 2008 to 2010 and Minister of Trade from 2011 to 2012. He was born in Espiritu Santo, then-New Hebrides. Molisa died on 21 August 2022 in Port Vila, Vanuatu at the age of 71. ==References== Category:1950 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Vanuatuan people Category:Oceanic politicians
